    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-24T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-24T02:00:00-05:00" n="577"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00B/8–2449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jones</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-24T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 24, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 24—9:40 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1885. Bearing upon extent to which CCP draws inspiration from Sun Yat-sen
                    doctrine as against Marxism–Leninism–Stalinism, we <pb facs="0513" n="503"
                        xml:id="pg_503"/> note that to best of our knowledge Chinese Communists have
                    held no commemoratory services or celebrations at Sun Yat-sen mausoleum since
                    their take-over of Nanking last April. Neither have we heard of Sun’s picture
                    being used at public meetings as are those of Lenin, Stalin, Mao and Chu.<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d577fn3">Chu Teh, Commander in Chief of Chinese Communist
                        armies.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Department 1885; repeated Shanghai 1036, Canton 793.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jones</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
